This follows the recent withdrawal of Nigerian basketball teams from all International competitions for the period of two years by President Muhammadu Buhari due to the unending leadership crisis rocking the Nigeria Basketball Federation (NBBF). Dr Henry Nzekwe, an accomplished public sector expert is the head of the committee saddled with the responsibility of reviving the moribund state of Nigeria domestic basketball league and attracting corporate sponsorship for the development of the sport in the country. Other members of the committee are: Mr. Udon Ubon Humapwa, Mrr. Frank Jitubhoh, Zenith Bank – Representative, Prof. Adamu Ahmed, Mr. Peter Nelson, Group Captain Rahinatu Garba, Aderemi Adewunmi, Oluchi Nzekwe and Sani Adio (SAN). The Sports Ministry in a statement by director of press and public relation, Mohammed Manga, said the committee is to draw up programmes that will revamp Nigeria’s basketball from the grassroots and revive its moribund domestic leagues.